Danielle starred in the reality television show Married to Jonas, which was about her marriage to Kevin Jonas, a Jonas Brother. The show debuted in 2012 and ran for two seasons. Danielle's main story line in the first season focused on her tumultuous relationship with her mother-in-law, Denise Jonas. Danielle Jonas was born in Denville Township, New Jersey on September 18, 1986. She has two sisters and one brother. She attended Morris Knolls High School. She worked as a hairdresser before meeting Kevin Jonas. In late 2013, Danielle Jonas and her husband partnered with Dreft to launch an app called Amazing Baby Days that allows couples to capture all of the moments from their pregnancy through the first year of a child's life. She live tweeted the birth of her first daughter as a part of the Dreft partnership.